This seems like an issue of the user interface to the domain system,
rather than a problem with the domain system itself.  Programs are free to
try various ways of completing a name like "y.ecn".  The presence of a
period does not have to imply that it is a full domain name.

In your example, running at host w.cs.purdue.edu, a fully general program
not knowing anything a priori about the host it is running at might try
y.ecn.w.cs.purdue.edu, y.ecn.cs.purdue.edu, y.ecn.purdue.edu, y.ecn.edu,
and y.ecn.  The first case could come up if a domain both names a host and
has subdomains, which might happen somewhere.

Completion queries might help with this, though their implementation in
servers is optional.

						Joe

